whOo/phew : just paleobio left >_<

You know what's crazy? In situations when things are great, there's still limitless stress. I was contemplating why I can't find myself in the good times anymore. Opportunities are finally being flung into my face (what I've been waiting for and what everyone has been talking about) and I'm still going bananas! So bananas, that I went home mid-finals week purely so I could lay on my parents' bed and tell them that I want them to drive me around and pull the meat off the bones/out of shells and bring me snacks when I'm in class. I went home to hear them tell me that they still would --- and that's what makes me strong enough to keep stressing. Can't stop loving the family and friends!
Anywho .. I was thinking again that maybe I'm all screwed up now and am anti-happy girl, not capable of just being. Depressing isn't it? BUT I realized that God made it THIS way because if I was deliriously happy right now, I'd fall on my face and really be up the butt. When you're at the top, there's no way but down. I can't afford to go down right now.

and hey.. CONGRATULATIONS to all the grads! Don't worry, opportunities will be flung in your face too. Just catch one at a time, school's in the bag!

Anyway, today was a superbly great day, hence my logging of it via livejournal. Although I had an Ochem midterm, it was lovely (minus the two reagents I didn't know and NMR). I got my lab job!!!!!! That's a big thumbs up! .. so tomorrow I get to go in and tell them when I can start working and what days. I'm excited! I haven't had a job in almost two years!!! (dorky aren't I?) PLUS I have an interview to work at a biotech company in their organic lab .. PLUS I have an interview with a clothing place downtown! The busier I am the more I get done - it's proven to be true in the past, so better grades here I come!
wOw .. my boat finally came in!

ALLLLRIGHT, after being delirious all day talking about chem in physics and dreaming about mechanisms it's BIO time! :D I love school! .. and daniel!

This may be mean, but the truth is hardly ever nice. 
People are stupid. Sometimes I wonder why because I believe that all people have a choice in life. Option A: Use your abilities to become everything that you want to be. Your brain is there; use it. or Option B: Be a giant lazy butt that complains about being stupid (about how it's not your fault, but think JUST for a second: it is). Get over it and pick your butt up!

I can't change the ignorant people because in the long run they're the most apt to not listen. I know I'm not ever going to be the smartest person in the world and maybe I'm not the best person for advice, but at least I don't think I'm stupid. I'm confident and I think that intimidates people. When I want something I'm logical: How will I get there? What's the best route? Is it worth it? Then I go. Hopefully, the people I love will keep up with me, otherwise I'll go first and come back to help.

I ate and ate and ate today. Well...not so much, but I went to Fuji's Sushi Buffet :D (early birthday present to myself) I went with Matt my cOol Indonesian friend - we're math geniuses, or more like he's the genius and I'm the understudy. Anyhow, we ate as much as we could and then got a coffee and talked. I admit it was really refreshing getting out of the routine of life.
Now, while I should be studying, I'm learning that I'm not as computer literate as I thought. It's sad.

I just got back to Davis from my two day excursion to the bay! What a trip huh? I loved being home. I forgot how wonderful it is to walk barefoot on clean carpet, have a fridge full of food, and see faces of people who truly absolutely undoubtedly love me!

Some days out of the blue I am reminded of how blessed I am. Today I looked at my life and saw beauty. I have everything I need and extras.
What I didn't see, until today, are the people who are envious of what I have.
There's always someone trying to bring you down >_<

I can't sleep through the night anymore. I wake up on the hour. Then, morning rolls around and a surge of adrenaline pumps through my body and I shoot up for the day. No naps. No rests. Just awake.
I feel bad because I make Daniel stay up with me because I know he knows that I know he coaxes me to sleep :] I'm like a weird human puppy.
